      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Well, this is&amp;nbsp;a toughie isn't it? Have to satisfy the majority i guess. When my friends and I heard of the progression server, one thing came to mind. Starting from the beginning. So what is the goal here? To go through every expansion to experience it again? To the folks who never experienced the beginning of the game, it was awesome. Just to get on and go kill a few ghouls at the undead ruins in EC or go to EC cave and look at Bags of stuff people are selling at first torch because there wasn't a&amp;nbsp;bazaar. It was simple. So no matter how hard this is, its something people want; its something i want. Now how do we actually progress on a progression server? Thats simple too. How did we progress in the first place? Yes granted it will take a while to get to luclin and my beloved Vex Thall zone but to love the game again you have to start with EQ classic and give everyone time and chance to enjoy it. Once the highest tier of zones in Classic have been conquered for the first time, wait a month or so then bring out Kunark. That way, more people will have progressed enough to tackle Kunark with Seblis, Veeshan's Peak, and the other wonders there. Set a moderate flow with these expansions...not too long not too short. Flagging is great and all but was it in the beginning? No. So it shouldnt be there. Having to use a ship and paying wizards and druids for ports to get anywhere. The what we call 'hardships' we call now was just a part of the game then. That is the EQ i remember. I like EQ, but i use to really love it. If you put too much of the modern EQ in this there will be no point.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I do like the idea of stopping the progression of expansions at some point. Planes of power would be a great place to stop. It will take a long time for VT to be in competition of guilds...when you have 5 guilds who could all do a VT cycle, then its time to expand to PoP. This is a good chance for you, SoE, to fix what you regret or didnt think really worked. But the point is, no one really wants LoY or discord or Omens. They can do that on their home servers. Granted that by the time you could expand to that, every other server will have other expansions to keep them occupied. So if Progression really is a hit when PoP comes out, then maybe you should think to make different expansions that even the regular servers dont have. Just something to think about.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Uglofis - The Seventh Hammer&lt;/P&gt;</description>
