      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I love the idea of this server but I wish that some things were different. I wish hell levels would stay in. I wish the boats would work and I wish the old things people considered 'a pain' were still in the game. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I know that hell levels were hard and people say "waaahhh i wanna be level 70 with 10 million aa points now" but seriously, things like that are what made the game a challenge. They were put there for a reason when the game was first released. It was obviously successful when these types of things were in before. Things like this are what made the game a success. They pulled the community together. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;People say "You're never going to recapture that feeling of when you first started" Well of course you can't. But the feeling of community could be recaptured. THAT is what made the game good. Zoning into somewhere and saying where the heck am I this is so cool was fun but that isn't what made players stay for 5+ years. It was the community and the challenge of the game. Feeling like if you screw up something bad will actually happen. I mean shoot, if you are just playing to powerlevel you might as well go play oblivion or something and save yourself the monthly fee. I for one am all for hell levels, working boats, looking at your spell book, bartering, asking for ports or walking and all the things that were part of the original and well thought out game. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Good luck sony I hope you can give a sense of community again.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
